name: Glitch of Retour de Voyage II (Leonor Fini, 1985)
description: The original 1985 painting by Fini was unique in that it was less sexual than some of her earlier works, showing a woman sitting peacefully before an oriental screen. The glitched work, like the original, presents a dream-like quality that could be representative of an artist who, in their maturity, has reached enlightenment (Fini was 78 when she painted the piece), or an artist waiting at the doorway to death.
